pact of multiple disabilities over time and on the phases of life. The book highlights the meaning of care in unexplored contexts, such as where ageing parents are caregivers or regarding mutual care in disabled couples. These are areas of knowledge which have, to date, been totally neglected.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aOlder people with disabilitiesxCare. 0aOlder people with disabilities. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gerontology.2bisacsh1 aBülow, Per, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrassman, Eva Jeppsson, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHolme, Lotta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJeppsson Grassman, Eva, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLarsson, Annika Taghizadeh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPhillips, Judith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSvensson, Tommy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTorgé, Cristina Joy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWhitaker, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWhitaker, Anna, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995z9783111196213oZDB-23-BUPP0 cprintz978144730522440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447305231423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447305231/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-BUPPc1995d2013